<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 8:54AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>Light snow will continue to fall through 10 or 11 AM. An
additional light coating of accumulation is expected on area
roadways, especially secondaries and untreated roads. Temperatures
are also below freezing which could create slick spots where snow
may have initially melted. Use extra caution if traveling this
morning as slippery conditions are expected. Temperatures are
expected to rise above freezing this afternoon which should
result in some snowmelt.</description>
